Automated Tool	wpscan with --enumerate and API key	Confirm version, themes, plugins, and users
âœ… If This, Then That: WordPress Enumeration
If robots.txt or /wp-login.php exists â†’ Then itâ€™s WordPress.

If meta tag includes version â†’ Then cross-check on wpvulndb.com or use wpscan.

If plugins/themes show in page source â†’ Then attempt to enumerate their version with curl or readme.txt.

If directory listing is enabled on /wp-content â†’ Then manually explore or fuzz with ffuf.

If /wp-login.php gives different errors for valid/invalid usernames â†’ Then you can brute force users.

If /xmlrpc.php is accessible â†’ Then use wpscan XML-RPC login method for faster bruteforce.

